This style‚Ä¶ it is a homage and direct adaptation of the presentation of our founding forefathers of old. The historical Burrs, and others. I have cultivated it as the culmination of several years of public relations research, to look respectable, dignified, classy.

A binding falls to the ground.

‚Ä¶There is no point. There is no public. There will be no domain, if I fail here.

And in all my confrontations up to now‚Ä¶ I‚Äôve kept this the way it was, even as I occasionally was slowed by the unwieldiness of parts of my presentation, uninvested in something as trivial as combat or some kind of cardio work.

But I can‚Äôt afford to hold back anymore.

It drapes down, unbound, wildly and uncouth, slightly past my shoulders. I can no longer care for aesthetics.

I grimace at the runt and his pitiful attempt at penetrating my skin.

More than something you can't prove, for more than something that means nothing. It's something I had to learn forcefully. I can't change how you feel but, think on that."

*Please. Don't...*
"I'm sorry!" He cries out, beside himself. "I'm sorry, mom, I'm sorry, I'm sorry..."

‚Äú*The apple doesn‚Äôt falls far from of from of the tree.* Wazy Emerson said that.‚Äù

"This empire shall rise into a new era of prosperity under my rule! I shall fix the course of history! You fools don‚Äôt deserve to witness my ascent, even you Nash! I‚Äôve sacrificed everything for our future and you‚Äôre all throwing away your lives to ruin it."
‚Äú‚Ä¶You sound like someone else I know.‚Äù I chuckle. ‚ÄúDuchess Selene, have you heard of Americium‚Ä¶?‚Äù I grin absurdly smugly.

"Shut. Your. Mouth, filth. Filthy, filthy, filthy! All of your kind are the same, filthy, filthy, filthy!!! You think you know what a 'future' is? You think you know what prosperity is? You are all the same, scum of the earth! Scum, scum, scum! You know nothing of this world, you know nothing what it's like to suffer, you know nothing what it's like to face death and accept it as the same as living. To not even be able to comprehend that life is death itself, that suicide is living, but that you must live on in order to make sure others don't see it the same way. Because if one thing *is* sacred, then it's justice. There's no place for justice in Soltaria. Because of filth. You make this world, this country a place where justice and hope doesn't exist!"
Selle to The Duchess.

((who's turn is it))
((aeolian i tihnk))

‚Äú‚Ä¶The truth is, this stuff is, eh‚Ä¶ kind of worthless. Very, very niche applications. What matters is the cultivated image of an alchemist-king. My ideals are what matter. But I keep them close to my chest. All while acting like someone who doesn‚Äôt ‚Äî while constantly explaining myself and elaborating. Saying a lot without saying anything at all. Evade suspicion as a schemer and deceiver by playing with your cards face up‚Ä¶ but have more cards you keep hidden.‚Äù

I throw a hunk of metal The Duchesses way, which is such a stupid pointless action I‚Äôm home brewing flavor texting it as how I activate the enhance weapon infusion on my dagger. Then I cast third level healing word on myself.
*What the fuck is he talking about...?*

‚ÄúI guess what I‚Äôm trying to say is‚Ä¶ I can‚Äôt know for sure that what you planned to wield power for was evil. It seems foolhardy and shortsighted to me, but we‚Äôre just political rivals. We don‚Äôt actually know each other. This was not a matter of righteousness, or fate.‚Äù

"All of my enemies fell apart‚Ä¶ Why did you both show up!? I just need a little more time‚Ä¶"

"Too bad for you, I have all the time in the world."

‚ÄúYou know, it‚Äôs funny, I was thinking the same thing just recently. Time‚Ä¶ a powerful force. There was this guy who kept asking me to solve the assassination attempt on the emperor, and last night they were speaking in the realm of, here‚Äôs your last chance. And I could only respond, look, I barely have any idea, do you understand all the nonsense that has occurred these past few days? I was certain with more time I could have happened upon a better answer‚Ä¶ anyway, time‚Ä¶ sure is something.‚Äù I yawn. ‚ÄúBy the way, do any of you know who did that?‚Äù
Selle chuckles at that question.

"Ffffuuuuck you..." Nash spits. It's hopeless. He knows it's hopeless. He knows it won't go anywhere. He knows he's going to die here *But.. the look on her face. The smug fuuucking proselytizing, like you know me better than I know me... fuck you. Die. Die. Eat shit and die, you fucking bitch, I can't, I can't, I can't, Mom, I need, I...*
He swings his longsword at Selle.
5 to hit. Wow, he's really not doing well.
‚ÄúLike, was it just you, Selene? Or a proxy working for you? That would be annoying. I had sort of discounted it internally out of fear I‚Äôd only conclude such a thing via bias.‚Äù
((I SHOULD HAVE ASKED AEOLIAN TO HEAL ME)
((There is no fucking way a 5 hits you.))
(( ignore  that im stupid)
((Not 5 damage lol))
"What are you even referring to?" She snarls.
Is that the end of Nash‚Äôs turn?
"No, I know the killer. But, who that is doesn't matter anymore. Some bad experiences, some good ones, you could say. It doesn't matter anymore. The only thing that matters is stopping *her*."
Yes.
‚ÄúMm. You won‚Äôt say‚Ä¶? It wasn‚Äôt Lydia, right? It would be incredibly personally embarrassing for me if it was her. Or THE QUEEN as she tries to be called, I guess.‚Äù
"Hah, as if the Hellhounds would have a mind to do that kind of thing."
‚ÄúGood, alright. Sure. I guess I‚Äôll learn one day. My last theory was that it was a suicide attempt, which, honestly, I think I was just venting at my lack of knowledge. That‚Äôs so dumb.‚Äù
"Enough games." Her sceptre shoots beams of light at all her enemies. ((11 damage to all 3 of you))
Selle goes down.
Darn. This truly does lower my health quite a bit, without knocking me out.
"Filth!" Selle yells as their legs give out.
This knocks Nash to near-death, again.
He hits the ground with a thud, blood running into his eyes.
I look at Nash collapse and glare at the Duchess, shaking my head. ‚Äú*Don‚Äôt bite the feed that you hands.* - Wazy Emerson (Accurate direct translation to modern common is impossible.)‚Äù

"Just you and me, Baron. Let‚Äôs finish this." She grins.

*Slash*

Her sceptre splits in half, the magical part hitting the ground with a dull thud.

"That‚Äôs enough. You lose, Duchess." Emperor Aragon is standing with a sword in hand, having just cleaved her weapon in half. "Checkmate."

((Initiative ends. Everyone gets 700xp))
‚ÄúEn passant.‚Äù I say this.
((You guys are awake enough to see this for the record you‚Äôre back up to 1hp or whatever))
"Mom..!" Nash tries to stand up and immediately falls back down.
"Urgh... What a fucking mess."

"Emperor‚Ä¶ But you‚Äôre supposed to be in a coma!" The Duchess.

"Yes. A trap of sorts. And you couldn‚Äôt resist." He speaks with an air of confidence as he snaps his fingers.

Harriet Dana Edwardson and The Endless Eclipse both exit stealth. The former looks dissociated beyond imagination and the latter just looks kind of amused.

"I needed you to give me reason to remove you from our country without repercussions. Thank you for providing it." Aragon smiles.
"Hhngh.. huh?" Nash is, like, barely conscious.
Who the FUCK is the Endless Eclipse.
Wait, I remember, alright.
Selle is actually, kind of upset about this but is too incapacitated to vocalise it.
(( this is a fucking cold steel 2 ass plot point atmey

"What‚Ä¶?" The Duchess drops her weapon.

"There were, of course, other aspects to this plan. A loyalty test, of sorts. Congratulations to the 3 of you who answered the call and arrived here. Aeolian, I‚Äôd assume this was the Queen‚Äôs work. The other 2, I haven‚Äôt the faintest clue. So perhaps congratulations are in order." Aragon.
*What????*
‚ÄúWell, shoot, now I just sort of feel like I‚Äôm the one‚Ä¶‚Äù I look around. ‚ÄúI mean, I guess she had no actual chance of winning?‚Äù
"No wonder things felt out of my control."

‚ÄúNo, Nash‚Ä¶‚Äù Oh, whatever. Let him mess this up for himself if he wants.

‚ÄúI‚Äôm not, loyal, I just‚Ä¶‚Äù I mutter.
Nash spits up some more blood. "Mom, I..."
‚ÄúWashington tipped me off about the Duchess this morning. I ultimately believed him, for whatever reason.‚Äù

‚ÄúWash‚Ä¶ oh, shit. Fuck, the queen. They took‚Äî‚Äù His composure shatters. ‚ÄúThey, they have‚Ä¶ I thought dealing with this might resolve that, but, the queen, she‚Äôs, she took my, she has, she‚Ä¶‚Äù

"Nash Edwardson... I've had my eye on you since you and your team came to me. Aeolian Burr, I've heard quite a lot about your exploits. But the last one, I've truly never seen you in my life." Aragon sighs in a way reminiscent of disappointment but not quite exactly. "I was not lying about the test of loyalty, I assure you all. I am going to fix our country... And then the world. There are of course 2 options present for you here." He takes out a flute looking object and plays it. Strange note shaped darts burrow into each of your necks. This does no damage beyond a mild prick. "You cannot run anymore. This allows me to see wherever you are in the world. So the next question is, of course... Do you wish to work for me or follow the Duchess?"

Harriet approaches Nash. "Trust me, Nash... Please... You can't fight this." She sounds tired.
‚ÄúOw. What? I don‚Äôt care. Where‚Äôs Aliza? Follow the Duchess? Where is she going? Exile?‚Äù
He looks around, suddenly overwhelmed. ‚ÄúI‚Äôm not, I didn‚Äôt, ah, that would be‚Ä¶‚Äù
"I can't..." Nash is on the verge of a panic attack, hands gripping his head. "She's my *mom,* I can't, I can't, she needs me, I'm, she..."

"Nash Edwardson... Your people need you. I spoke with your sister. I believe your other mother will need you just as well. But if you truly desire it... I am willing to spare your mother's life for an alliance. You have, after all, passed the necessary qualifications." Aragon turns to Aeolian. "You, baron... I do not know who Aliza is but if it is within my control, I am willing to see what I can do about her." 

"She's just that girl The Queen's got an eye for. She's fine." The Devil of Soltaria, who is just another title for The Endless Eclipse and thus referring to the same character, scoffs dismissively.
He raises his tearstained face up to Aragon. "My.. people? I don't, I don't have people, I just have my family, and they're, I, I... an alliance? What does that mean, I don't understand, mom, I..."

"Ghrk. Again, taking the control from me. Again, forcing me to have to secede to the whims of fate. Tell me, Aragon, what do you think of *justice*? Do you think that your vision of the world, as a "great man" will let you make it a reality? Because, I feel as though, as long as there exist "kings" and "rulers", "gods" and "priests", then there truly is no such thing as *justice*. So why, why would you test someone who believes their life is nothing but a tool to invoke their ideals onto the world to work with them? The first time I got that dream, I told the dragon that the only reason I accepted, was because my life had already almost ended twice that day."
Selle manages to regurgitate this through their near-fatal wounds.

‚ÄúEye fo‚Äî what? What does that mean? What?‚Äù I stare at the ground. ‚ÄúI mean, I guess it‚Äôs fine if‚Ä¶ no, what?‚Äù I close my eyes and shake my head. ‚ÄúAh, I mean, if she‚Äôs alive, that‚Äôs‚Ä¶‚Äù What?
You all can keep talking, it‚Äôs fine, Aeolian‚Äôs just thinking.

"I see." He looks at Selle with disinterest and turns back to Nash. "I believe you can do a lot for your country, Nash. That you can live with purpose. And that one day... You may die with purpose. Is that not your goal? The favored priestess of your goddess and your sister sides with me. Do you truly believe my plans to be the wrong direction? I have brought stability to this empire by removing the pieces I could not control and turning those that I could into an army of good. Don't you want to see what your goddess has in store for you under me?'"
"I..." he hiccups. "Would she really... be spared?"

"Pfft." Selle starts to laugh maniacally. "Nobody hears me! Hahahahahaha! That's so fucking funny! Hear me, hear me, world, there's nothing left! Nothing here, nothing there! Hahahahahahahahaha!
